annotation 1 [0.82, 0.08] DIFFERENTIATORS: OWL 2 ontology reasoning (rare in this space), GPU-accelerated graph physics, and Nostr-based decentralised identity. These are custom/genesis components that competitors lack.
annotation 2 [0.45, 0.55] PRODUCT LAYER: Claude-Flow orchestration, WebXR frontend, and vector memory are structured capabilities built on commodity infrastructure. These could be replicated but the integration is the moat.
annotation 3 [0.15, 0.70] COMMODITY: Standard infrastructure (PostgreSQL, NVIDIA GPUs, Neo4j) that anyone can procure. Not differentiating.

note All components verified against codebase April 2026. Previous claims (101 skills, multi-provider orchestration, W3C DIDs, 100K nodes) have been corrected to verified reality. [0.05, 0.40]
